title: 160 years later, S.F.’s 1st fire engine returns
text:
Photo: Nathaniel Y. Downes, The Chronicle Alan Camarillo brings the newly acquired fire engine back to its resting place in the museum after being on display in the morning on Wednesday, Oct. 7, 2015 in San Francisco, Calif. San Francisco Fire Department Museum sees the return of the cities first ever fire engine built in 1855. Alan Camarillo brings the newly acquired fire engine back to its...
One of the oldest fire engines in the West, a curious little vehicle of iron, brass and polished wood, has come home to San Francisco, 160 years after it put out its first fire.
